project LRUCache

task LeastRecentlyUsedCache
    goal
        A fixed-capacity LRU cache with get, put, and size.
    output
        cache_state
    constraint
        Class name is LRUCache.
        Module is impl.py.
        Constructor takes a single positional argument capacity.
    test
        A newly constructed cache reports size 0.
        put adds an entry and size reflects the count.
        get returns the value for a stored key.
        get on a missing key raises KeyError.
        put on an existing key replaces the value.
        put on an existing key does not grow the size.
        put beyond capacity evicts the least-recently-used entry.
        get renews recency so a subsequent put evicts a different entry.
        Capacity zero raises ValueError.
        Negative capacity raises ValueError.
        Non-int capacity raises TypeError.
    success
        Every acceptance case above matches exactly.
